tr.td: Title: OV: grief, HTN
Author: Akande MD, Olusina

1. Prolonged grief disorder F43.81
Chronic, stable.
Assessment: Counseled the patient that she does need to start going to a grief share group to deal with some of the feelings that she is having as it is causing other comorbidities, most prominently issues with insomnia.
Meds: No current changes in management.
Labs: N/A
Imaging: N/A
Referral: N/A
Counseling: N/A
2. Vertigo R42
Chronic, stable.
Assessment: The patient has several different comorbidities that could be contributing including history of stroke and symptoms of anxiety and depression relating to her prolonged grief.
Meds: No current changes in management
Labs: N/A
Counseling: Counseled the patient on performing the Epley maneuver to decrease the frequency of her symptoms.
3. Essential hypertension I10
Chronic, stable.
Assessment: EKG is on file and labs were reviewed during the appointment.
Meds: The patient will continue to take lisinopril and amlodipine.
Labs: N/A
Imaging: N/A
Referral: N/A
Counseling: Lifestyle changes such as low salt diet, activity, and excess alcohol.
4. Insomnia G47.00
Chronic, stable.
Assessment: A result of the patient's issues with grief that she has not dealt with.
Meds: The patient will continue to take trazodone without any changes in management other than starting to go to a grief share group.
Labs: N/A
Counseling: N/A
5. Keratoconus H18.609
The patient will continue to follow up with her ophthalmologist.
6. Bilateral cataracts H26.9

Chief Complaint
6 mo follow up
History of Present Illness
Vickie Berry is a 70-year-old female who presents to the office today for a follow-up visit. The patient has approved the use of DAX for the recording of this visit and the creation of documentation.
Prolonged grief disorder
The patient would like to discuss counseling. She notes that she has not tried counseling in the past. The patient mentions her mom and dad both died the same week from 10 years ago. She states her granddaughter also died 8 years ago. The patient reports her husband just got arrested for the third time for drunk driving. She reports that her husband was recently moped, and she is concerned that he will not leave. She notes that her husband has PTSD. She reports that her youngest son was diagnosed with Parkinson's disease approximately 1 year ago. She notes that she is afraid for her daughter to be 34 years old. She reports that she quit going to church because she does not know if she believes in God anymore.
Insomnia
The patient notes that she sleeps well. She reports that she takes trazodone. She notes that she wakes up at 4:30 AM and is unable to get back to sleep.
Vertigo
The patient reports that she has been experiencing dizziness for a few years. She notes that she will go 2 to 3 weeks without experiencing dizziness. She reports that she has not had a headache in approximately 10 years.
Keratoconus
The patient reports that she has keratoconus. She notes that she cannot see without contacts. She reports that she went 4 weeks without contacts. She notes that she was measured to have her cataracts off and was told that she had a stroke. She reports that she was told that she needed to follow up with her neurologist.

Meds: No current changes in management
Labs: N/A
Counseling: Counseled the patient on performing the Epley maneuver to decrease the frequency of her symptoms.
3. Essential hypertension I10

Counseling: Lifestyle changes such as low salt diet, activity, and excess alcohol.
4. Insomnia G47.00

Meds: The patient will continue to take trazodone without any changes in management other than starting to go to a grief share group.
